articles.author: Tom Nicholson
articles.title: Kosovo PM Albin Kurti wins election amid tensions with Brussels and Washington - POLITICO Europe
articles.description: His ruling party fell short of a majority and will need to find a coalition partner if it hopes to continue in power.
articles.content:
“Everything went according to plan,” Kurti said following the election. “We won, and this is confirmation of a good, prosperous and democratic government.”
